                &#91;Hebrew&#93;<lb/></p>
                
                <pb n="2"/> 
            <p>Questions for Rev. Mr. Morais to<lb/> answer and explain at the Teachers&#39;<lb/> Meeting Monday Eve. Nov. 3rd 1884.<lb/></p>
                
            <p>1st. What course of instruction would<lb/> you suggest for a teacher in the<lb/> Sunday School to pursue&#44; who wishes<lb/> in a limited time to teach the<lb/> principles of the Jewish Religion to<lb/> a class of children&#63;</p>
            <p>Principles &#38; not creeds may be learned chiefly from Deuteronomy&#8212;the spirit of Judaism<lb/> from various books of Grace Aguilar<lb/></p>
            <p>2. What was the <sic>origon</sic> and mean&#45;<lb/> ing of the title &#34;Morenu.&#34;&#63;<lb/></p>
            <p>Explain the origins of titles &#91;Hebrew&#93; &#38; then &#91;Hebrew&#93;<lb/></p>
                
                <pb n="3"/>
            <p>3. The term Go&#45;al &#40;in Hebrew&#41; in Ruth 4.&#45;14&#91;&#63;&#93;<lb/> has been translated meaning &#34;Redeemer.&#34; <lb/> Please explain the significance of<lb/> the term.<lb/></p>
            <p>&#91;Hebrew&#93; to buy back&#44; in case of property disposed of through poverty&#44;<lb/> to purchase back to freedom&#44; in case of people having been &#91;&#63;&#93; enslaved&#44; to mar&#45;<lb/> ry&#44; means of the widow being childless and destitute.</p>
            <p>4. Please give some account of the<lb/> various translations of the Bible&#44;<lb/> especially of those under Hebrew<lb/> authority. &#91;in pencil&#58;&#93; Think of the Setuagent &#38; of the saying  of the Tal&#45;<lb/>mudists on it&#8212;of Onkelos and  Aguilar&#45;&#45;of Jonathan and  Joseph the &#91;&#63;&#93;<lb/> Refer to the Peshite&#91;&#63;&#93; &#38; of the various English versions. &#91;&#63;&#93; in 1382<lb/> seems to be the first who translated the whole Bible in English. It is found in some<lb/> rare libraries<lb/></p>
            <p>5.Are there extant&#44; any Hebrew<lb/> books contemporary with the<lb/> books of the Bible&#63;<lb/></p>
            <p>The Bible is the  oldest book. Speak of the book of &#34;the &#91;&#63;&#93; of<lb/> the Lord&#34; &#38; the book &#34;Yoshar&#91;&#63;&#93;&#34;&#45;&#45; of cuneiform writings &#91;&#63;&#93;<lb/> allegories &#38; corroborating in a great measure Holy Writ<lb/></p>
                
                
